                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-20T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Your 248, September 19, 5 p.m., paragraph 5.<note n="55" xml:id="d117fn55"
                        >Not printed.</note> You are correct in your assumption that in the event
                    that an inquiry is officially made of you, you may state that the United States
                    will be unable to accept membership on any League commission which may be
                    appointed to deal with the Chaco problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
